# Session branch hygiene

Full SSOT: EngineerID/ambient-systems company/strategy/governance/ecosystem-branching.md

Local short form: docs/hub/branching.md

## Main safety

- Never commit or push to main. Even one-line fixes use repo/short-kebab-scope plus a PR.
- Never force-push main. Prefer small scoped PRs.

## Existing work isolation

1. Before the first new commit, inspect working-tree changes, commits not on main, and open PRs.
2. If an existing commit or user change belongs to another task, verify its PR state and keep it separate. Never amend it or include it in the new task commit or PR.
3. If the primary worktree is dirty or on another active branch, create an isolated worktree and new repo/* branch from updated origin/main.
4. Give the new task its own commit and PR. Report unrelated PRs separately unless the user asks to resolve them.

## Session close-out

1. After summarizing completed work and creating its commit, immediately push the branch and open or update its PR into main.
2. When required checks are green and the user asked for the work, merge the PR in the same session.
3. A committed task is not closed until its PR is merged or explicitly abandoned.
4. After merge: confirm the remote head is deleted, fetch with prune, delete the local repo/* branch and isolated worktree, and return the primary worktree to updated main.
5. If abandoning: close the PR, delete the remote and local branches and isolated worktree, prune, and return the primary worktree to updated main.
6. Before the final response, list open PRs and non-main branches. Delete orphan hub-sync or cursor heads if auto-delete missed them.
7. Prefer one open repo/* PR; do not leave a ready in-session PR after the session.
